channel.title: Tech
channel.description: This is a randomly ordered feed of the most recent entries from Tech, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Wing to expand drone delivery to another 150 Walmart stores
item.description: The partnership will grow Wing's drone delivery service to more than 270 Walmart stores by 2027.

item.title: Google announces a new protocol to facilitate commerce using AI agents
item.description: Google said that merchants can now offer discounts to users directly in AI mode results

item.title: Indonesia and Malaysia block Grok over non-consensual, sexualized deepfakes
item.description: Indonesian officials said Saturday that they are temporarily blocking access to xAI’s chatbot Grok.

item.title: The 50 Best Movies on Netflix, WIRED’s Picks (January 2026)
item.description: Good Night, and Good Luck: Live From Broadway, Frankenstein, and Wake Up Dead Man: A Knives Out Mystery are just a few of the movies you should watch ...

item.title: Fujifilm X-E5 Mirrorless Camera Review: Compact Color Science in a Retro Package
item.description: Did you want the TikTok-popular X100VI, but with an interchangeable lens? The Fujifilm X-E5 has you covered.

item.title: Best Deals for New Year’s Resolutions: Sleep, Fitness, and More (2026)
item.description: Whether you’re hitting the gym or tracking your schedule, these discounts on WIRED-approved gear can help.

item.title: The 50 Best Shows on Netflix, WIRED's Picks (January 2026)
item.description: Stranger Things, Run Away, and His & Hers are just a few of the shows you need to watch on Netflix this month.

item.title: SpaceX gets FCC approval to launch 7,500 more Starlink satellites
item.description: The Federal Communications Commission has given SpaceX approval to launch another 7,500 of its second generation Starlink satellites.

item.title: OpenAI is reportedly asking contractors to upload real work from past jobs
item.description: An intellectual property lawyer says OpenAI is "putting itself at great risk" with this approach.

item.title: ICE Can Now Spy on Every Phone in Your Neighborhood
item.description: Plus: Iran shuts down its internet amid sweeping protests, an alleged scam boss gets extradited to China, and more.
